<h2>Send an SMS</h2>
<p>This <a href="https://developer.vonage.com/en/messages/code-snippets/sms/send-sms" target="_blank">sends an SMS</a> using the <a href="https://developer.vonage.com/en/messages/overview" target="_blank">Vonage Messages API</a>.</p>

<form action="/sms/create" method="post">
  <label for="number">Number: </label>
  <input
    id="number"
    type="text"
    name="number" />
  <label for="message">Message: </label>
  <textarea id="message" name="message"></textarea>
  <input type="submit" value="Send" />
</form>
<p class="notice">Note that there are specific regulations around sending SMS in India, and numbers need to be registered. See <a href="https://api.support.vonage.com/hc/en-us/articles/204017423-India-SMS-Features-and-Restrictions" target="_blank">India SMS Features and Restrictions
</a> for more information.</p>
<p class="notice">Note also that the code in the <code>create</code> controller under <code>/controllers/sms.js</code> is that standard code for sending an SMS. For sending SMS in India, you may need to include additonal parameters in the message body such as <code>sms.content_id</code> and/ or <code>sms.entity_id</code>. See the <a href="https://developer.vonage.com/en/api/messages-olympus" target="_blank">Messages API Reference</a> for more information.</p>
